sfrapTrap.description: A sfrapTrap trap signifies that the sending node had its `sfrapAlarmType` variable modified.

sfrapBadConfigTrap.name: sfrapBadConfigTrap
sfrapBadConfigTrap.description: Unit has received a configuration update request through SNMP but the request was rejected due to an incorrect or inappropriate parameter.

sfrapLocalConfigTrap.name: sfrapLocalConfigTrap
sfrapLocalConfigTrap.description: Unit configuration has been updated locally (console port or front panel keypad) or remotely (telnet).

sfrapLocalUnitLoopbackEnabledTrap.name: sfrapLocalUnitLoopbackEnabledTrap
sfrapLocalUnitLoopbackEnabledTrap.description: Unit is in a bidirectional unit loopback. Data is received from either interface, processed, and transmitted back towards the same interface. When configured for Frame Relay operation the unit will preserve the LMI path during this loopback. In Frame Relay mode, only valid frames are looped back (pseudorandom test patterns will be dropped).

sfrapLocalUnitLoopbackDisabledTrap.name: sfrapLocalUnitLoopbackDisabledTrap
sfrapLocalUnitLoopbackDisabledTrap.description: Bidirectional unit loopback path is removed.

sfrapLocalUnitLoopbackFailedTrap.name: sfrapLocalUnitLoopbackFailedTrap
sfrapLocalUnitLoopbackFailedTrap.description: Bidirectional unit loopback request has been rejected by the unit. Typically, this is due to the presence of another loopback condition.

sfrapLocalToDteLoopbackEnabledTrap.name: sfrapLocalToDteLoopbackEnabledTrap
sfrapLocalToDteLoopbackEnabledTrap.description: Unit is in a bidirectional TO-DTE loopback. All data received at the TO-DTE interface is looped back regardless of format or content (line loopback). When configured for Frame Relay operation the unit will not preserve the LMI path during this loopback. Data received from the TO-DCE is processed and transmitted back out the TO-DCE. In Frame Relay mode, on the TO-DCE interface, only valid frames are looped back (pseudorandom test patterns will be dropped).

sfrapLocalToDteLoopbackDisabledTrap.name: sfrapLocalToDteLoopbackDisabledTrap
sfrapLocalToDteLoopbackDisabledTrap.description: Bidirectional TO-DTE loopback path is removed.

sfrapLocalToDteLoopbackFailedTrap.name: sfrapLocalToDteLoopbackFailedTrap
sfrapLocalToDteLoopbackFailedTrap.description: Bidirectional TO-DTE loopback request has been rejected by the unit. Typically, this is due to the presence of another loopback condition.

sfrapDLCIActiveTrap.name: sfrapDLCIActiveTrap
sfrapDLCIActiveTrap.description: Unit is reporting this DLCI as active and provisioned. An active DLCI is one that is explictly declared ACTIVE in an LMI Full Status Response (typically coming from a frame relay switch).

sfrapDLCIInactiveTrap.name: sfrapDLCIInactiveTrap
sfrapDLCIInactiveTrap.description: Unit is reporting this DLCI as inactive. An inactive DLCI is determined inactive one of two ways: it is either explictly declared inactive in an LMI Full Status Response (typically coming from a frame relay switch) or a Full Status Response is not seen causing a Full Status Timer expiry. Having the unit's full status timer too low could result in the unit falsely declaring DLCIs inactive (then active again). This does not interfere with any data activity on the DLCI but could result in excessive traps.

sfrapDLCITDThresholdTrap.name: sfrapDLCITDThresholdTrap
sfrapDLCITDThresholdTrap.description: VNIP has measured a round-trip transit delay on this PVC to this peer which exceeds the user-defined threshold.

sfrapLmiSourcingChangePassthruTrap.name: sfrapLmiSourcingChangePassthruTrap
sfrapLmiSourcingChangePassthruTrap.description: Unit is not sourcing any LMI messages. If this state persists then LMI is up and the proper handshaking is occurring independent of the unit. This may also be a transient state if the unit is in an LMI hunt mode. If this trap occurs repeatedly, separated by other LMI sourcing states, the unit is not seeing any of the expected LMI messages from either interface. Check LMI type, connectivity, and configuration of associated equipment.

sfrapLmiSourcingChangeUserToDteTrap.name: sfrapLmiSourcingChangeUserToDteTrap
sfrapLmiSourcingChangeUserToDteTrap.description: Unit is acting as a source of LMI Status Requests (Link Integrity Verification, Keep Alive). If this state persists then the equipment attached to the TO-DTE interface is configured as a Frame Relay DCE but a companion Frame Relay DTE device is not seen out the TO-DCE. This could also be a transient state if the unit is in an LMI hunt mode. If this trap occurs repeatedly, separated by other LMI sourcing states, the unit is not seeing any of the expected LMI messages from either interface. Check LMI type, connectivity, and configuration of associated equipment.

sfrapLmiSourcingChangeNetToDteTrap.name: sfrapLmiSourcingChangeNetToDteTrap
sfrapLmiSourcingChangeNetToDteTrap.description: Unit is acting as a source of LMI Status Responses (Link Intergrity Verification, Keep Alive). If this state persists then the equpiment attached to the TO-DTE interface is configured as a Frame Relay DTE but a companion Frame Relay DCE device is not seen out the TO-DCE. This could also be a transient state if the unit is in an LMI hunt mode. If this trap occurs repeatedly, separated by other LMI sourcing states, the unit is not seeing any of the expected LMI messages from either interface. Check LMI type, connectivity, and configuration of external equipment.

sfrapLmiSourcingChangeUserToDceTrap.name: sfrapLmiSourcingChangeUserToDceTrap
sfrapLmiSourcingChangeUserToDceTrap.description: Unit is acting as a source of LMI Status Requests (Link Integrity Verification, Keep Alive). If this state persists then the equipment attached to the TO-DCE interface is configured as a Frame Relay DCE but a companion Frame Relay DTE device is not seen out the TO-DTE interface. This could also be a transient state if the unit is in an LMI hunt mode. If this trap occurs repeatedly, separated by other LMI sourcing states, the unit is not seeing any of the expected LMI messages from either interface. Check LMI type, connectivity, and configuration of associated equipment.

sfrapLmiSourcingChangeNetToDceTrap.name: sfrapLmiSourcingChangeNetToDceTrap
sfrapLmiSourcingChangeNetToDceTrap.description: Unit is acting as a source of LMI Status Responses (Link Integrity Verification, Keep Alive). If this state persists then the equipment attached to the TO-DCE interface is configured as a Frame Relay DTE but a companion Frame Relay DCE device is not seen out the TO-DTE interface. This could also be a transient state if the unit is in an LMI hunt mode. If this trap occurs repeatedly, separated by other LMI sourcing states, the unit is not seeing any of the expected LMI messages from either interface. Check LMI type, connectivity, and configuration of associated equipment.

sfrapDteSignalRtsOnTrap.name: sfrapDteSignalRtsOnTrap
sfrapDteSignalRtsOnTrap.description: Unit's DTE Request to Send (RTS) interface control signal is now active (on). This signal is presented by the external DTE device. Unit may be configured to ignore the state of this signal or to require it for data transmission.

sfrapDteSignalRtsOffTrap.name: sfrapDteSignalRtsOffTrap
sfrapDteSignalRtsOffTrap.description: Unit's DTE Request to Send (RTS) interface control signal is now inactive (off). This signal is presented by the external DTE device. Unit may be configured to ignore the state of this signal or to require it for data transmission.

sfrapDteSignalDtrOnTrap.name: sfrapDteSignalDtrOnTrap
sfrapDteSignalDtrOnTrap.description: Unit's DTE Data Terminal Ready (DTR) interface control signal is now active (on). This signal is presented by the external DTE device. The unit may be configured to ignore the state of this signal or to require it for data transmission.

sfrapDteSignalDtrOffTrap.name: sfrapDteSignalDtrOffTrap
sfrapDteSignalDtrOffTrap.description: Unit's DTE Data Terminal Ready (DTR) interface control signal is now inactive (off). This signal is presented by the external DTE device. Unit may be configured to ignore the state of this signal or to require it for data transmission.

sfrapNonIncrLmiSeqNumToDteTrap.name: sfrapNonIncrLmiSeqNumToDteTrap
sfrapNonIncrLmiSeqNumToDteTrap.description: Unit has detected a non-incrementing LMI sequence number from the TO-DTE. A Status Enquiry or Status Response message has been seen at the TO-DTE interface. The Link Integrity information element's Send Sequence Number was not incremented or was incremented more than once since the last Send Sequence Number seen from the TO-DTE interface.

sfrapNonIncrLmiSeqNumToDceTrap.name: sfrapNonIncrLmiSeqNumToDceTrap
sfrapNonIncrLmiSeqNumToDceTrap.description: Unit has detected a non-incrementing LMI sequence number from the TO-DCE. A Status Enquiry or Status Response message has been seen at the TO-DCE interface. The Link Integrity information element's Send Sequence Number was not incremented or was incremented more than once since the last Send Sequence Number seen from the TO-DCE interface.

sfrapLmiSeqNumMismatchToDteTrap.name: sfrapLmiSeqNumMismatchToDteTrap
sfrapLmiSeqNumMismatchToDteTrap.description: Unit has detetcted an LMI sequence number mismatch from the TO-DTE. A Status Enquiry or Status Response message has been seen at the TO-DTE interface. The Link Inetgrity information element's Receive Sequence Number was not the most recent Send Sequence number sent from the TO-DCE interface.

sfrapLmiSeqNumMismatchToDceTrap.name: sfrapLmiSeqNumMismatchToDceTrap
sfrapLmiSeqNumMismatchToDceTrap.description: Unit has detetcted an LMI sequence number mismatch from the TO-DCE. A Status Enquiry or Status Response message has been seen at the TO-DCE interface.
